[~mdshaonimran] Ran the following three updates on the qa cloud as [~sjones] suspects the protocols are missing, causing the ingress rules to now show up:
{code}
eucalyptus_shared=# update eucalyptus_cloud.metadata_network_rule set version=version+1, metadata_network_rule_protocol_number=6 where metadata_network_rule_protocol_number is null and metadata_network_rule_protocol = 'tcp';
UPDATE 52
eucalyptus_shared=# update eucalyptus_cloud.metadata_network_rule set version=version+1, metadata_network_rule_protocol_number=1 where metadata_network_rule_protocol_number is null and metadata_network_rule_protocol = 'icmp';
UPDATE 20
eucalyptus_shared=# update eucalyptus_cloud.metadata_network_rule set version=version+1, metadata_network_rule_protocol_number=17 where metadata_network_rule_protocol_number is null and metadata_network_rule_protocol = 'udp';
UPDATE 6
eucalyptus_shared=# 
{code}

To get the ingressRules to push out you need to either restart eucalytpus-cloud (the CLC) or perform the following SQL update:
{code}
update eucalyptus_cloud.metadata_network_group set version = version + 1;
{code}

In our case restarting the CLC did the trick, the ingressRules shows up in the GNI (Global Network Info) broadcast.
